09/10/2006
IZMIR, Turkey -- Police said on Friday (October 6th) that they seized 4.1kg of plastic explosives and bomb diagrams from a private house in Izmir, apparently for use in a bomb plot.
One man, already convicted for supporting the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers' Party, was arrested.
Police say they found the explosives during an anti-drug operation.
In other news, the Albanian Interior Ministry announced on Sunday that police smashed a weapons trafficking ring from Albania to Greece.
Police seized three Kalashnikov automatic rifles from a car travelling on the Tirana-Elbasan road towards Greece, and confiscated ammunition from private houses.
Seven people were arrested.
(Albanian News - 09/10/06;
Zaman, Cihan - 06/10/06)
